.TH "update_mpp" 9 "update_mpp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
update_mpp \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" update_mpp
.BI "(u64 *entitlement "  ","
.BI "u8 *weight "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "entitlement" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "weight" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Update the memory entitlement and weight for the partition.  Caller must
specify either a new entitlement or weight, not both, to be updated
since the h_set_mpp call takes both entitlement and weight as parameters.
